reviews.review_text: pay more attention, kids All right, it has nothing to do with the fact that I was there, or what was "happening"... what was happening was Jerry on a really great night, knowing full well that his voice was not at it's best, and making up for it with his fingers - Please listen to this Terrapin - so much has been said about many other versions of this tune- it clocks in at 17+ minutes, and the jam post lyric is quintessential, definitive of this tour -listen especially to the transition to Don't Need Love, and the feeling that everyone onstage is emoting- Jerry and Brent's "conversation" musically is so enlightened and dynamic...well, I lose words to rave... If you want more, you should come by for the next night - ...

Noone does it better There are no better sounding shows out there then this crew here.I realize they had an in with the band.That it self helps but its the preserving and uploading and whatever editting done to these shows that makes then SPARLKE. I thank those involvled. 
 Sure does hurt my listening perspective have been to many of there recordings.
